//- Form checkbox mixin
//- Renders a configurable checkbox input with label.
//- Supports custom name, value, and checked state.
//-
//- Parameters:
//-   id       - **String** — Unique identifier for the <input> element.
//-              Also used by the <label> `for` attribute.
//-              Example: 'agree', 'subscribe'.
//-              Default: none (required).
//-   label    - **String** — Visible label text displayed next to the checkbox.
//-              Example: 'I agree to terms', 'Subscribe to newsletter'.
//-              Default: none (required).
//-   name     - **String** — Name attribute for grouping or form submission.
//-              Example: 'terms', 'preferences'.
//-              Default: ''.
//-   value    - **String** — Value submitted when the checkbox is checked.
//-              Example: 'yes', 'true', 'newsletter'.
//-              Default: 'on' (browser default).
//-   checked  - **Boolean** — Whether the checkbox is checked by default.
//-              Example: true, false.
//-              Default: false.
//-
//- Behavior:
//-   - Renders a `.form-group.form-check` wrapper for spacing and alignment.
//-   - The input always has `.form-check-input` class for styling.
//-   - The label always has `.form-label` class and is linked via `for=id`.
//-   - If `checked=true`, the checkbox is preselected.
//-   - The `value` is submitted only if the checkbox is checked.
//-
//- Notes about styling and classes:
//-   - Visual appearance is controlled by `.form-check-input` and `.form-label`
//-     styles in your SCSS.
//-   - To add custom classes or attributes, extend the mixin or wrap it.
//-   - Ensure `id` is unique to avoid duplicate `for`/`id` collisions.
//-
//- Examples:
//-   // Basic checkbox
//-   +formCheckbox('agree', 'I agree to all terms')
//-
//-   // Checkbox with custom name and value
//-   +formCheckbox('subscribe', 'Subscribe to newsletter', 'newsletter', 'yes')
//-
//-   // Checkbox checked by default
//-   +formCheckbox('updates', 'Receive updates', 'updates', 'true', true)
//-
//-   // Multiple checkboxes in a group
//-   .form-group
//-     span.form-label Preferences
//-     +formCheckbox('pref-email', 'Email notifications', 'preferences', 'email')
//-     +formCheckbox('pref-sms', 'SMS notifications', 'preferences', 'sms')
//-     +formCheckbox('pref-push', 'Push notifications', 'preferences', 'push')
mixin formCheckbox(id, label, name='', value='on', checked=false)
  .form-group.form-check
    input.form-check-input(
      type='checkbox',
      id=id,
      name=name,
      value=value,
      checked=checked
    )
    label.form-label(for=id)= label
